The paper deals with authentication and identification of IoT devices using machine learning techniques. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of machine learning algorithms for device identification suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper also discusses the methodology used for device fingerprinting, which may fall under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
